==English==

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /nɒk ʌp/

===Verb===
''' to [[knock]] [[up]]'''
# {{UK}}{{slang}} ''(archaic)'' To [[awaken]] someone in the [[morning]]
#:*'''1892''': “Very sorry to '''knock you up''', Watson,” said he, “but it's the common lot this morning.  Mrs. Hudson has been knocked up, she retorted upon me, and I on you.” — Arthur Conan Doyle, ‘The Adventure of the Speckled Band’ (Norton 2005 p.228)
# {{slang}}{{idiomcat}} To make someone [[pregnant]]
# {{UK}} To put together, particularly if done hastily or temporarily.
#: ''I'll just knock up a quick demo for the sales presentation.''

